<section id="ongoing-training">
<h2>Ongoing 1-on-1 Training</h2>
<p>
                    <strong>Duration:</strong> 1-1.5 hours per session
                </p>
<p>
                    Clients typically train between <strong>one to three times per week</strong>, depending on their goals and availability. Those who train more frequently tend to progress significantly faster and achieve more meaningful results. In all cases, adherence to the homework I prescribe between sessions is hugely beneficial to your progress.
                </p>
<p>
                    In these ongoing sessions, I will continually deepen my understanding of your body and how it moves, allowing me to efficiently address dysfunctions and improve your movement quality over time. Each session builds upon the last, creating a clear path of progression tailored specifically to you.
                </p>
<p>
                    <strong>Training packages are available</strong> and vary based on your level of commitment. Specific details regarding these packages can be discussed during your initial consultation.
